<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06157c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06157c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06157c"> 157(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> thoughts of my heart</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">PART IV. CHRISTIAN PRAYER. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> FIRST PETITION. <p>&ldquo;HALLOWED BE THY NAME.&rdquo;&mdash;Sanctified, treated as being holy and sacred. That the name of the one true God may be universally adored, and held sacred. That His holy name may be reverenced by the <mark>thoughts of our heart</mark>; by the words of our lips; by the work of our hands.&rdquo;</p> <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 43-4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
